If you have a grunt project and want to insert line number information into your files, you can now use the <a href="https://www.npmjs.org/package/grunt-line-number-plugin">grunt-line-number-plugin</a>.
This will turn this:
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">var myFunc = function myFunc() {
  // some code...
  doLog('Error in line __LINE__ D:');
  // moar code...
}</pre>
Into this:
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">var myFunc = function myFunc() {
  // some code...
  doLog('Error in line 3 D:');
  // moar code...
}</pre>
This might not make sense, since every decent js console implementation will tell you the line number right away. But a "real" console is not always available&hellip;

